      "writtenOn": "2020-07-27T20:40:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is kinda weird. When does Flush() need to be called? I don\u0027t see any documentation about this in output_stream_interface.h. If it needs to be called in this situation, shouldn\u0027t zlib_decompress_stream do that? If it doesn\u0027t need to be called, we should remove the DCHECK or only have it enabled in the cases where Flush() was required to be called.",
