        "id": 1000825
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-28T00:34:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I clarified the document, the flush must be called once write() succeeded.\n\nI think it has the side effect for the current OutputStream to call the Flush(), the next stream might be failed in this case, for example closing the uncompress operation, and this failure might cover the actual failure, beside this, it is also hard for the next stream to handle the successful Flush() but the whole pipeline failed.\n\nBy fixing this issue, the beneficiary might only be the false test case like this, we don\u0027t need to fail gracefully in this case :).",
      "parentUuid": "5bddb6d0_3e9d58ad",
      "range": {
